    <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 rounded-xl p-5 border border-brandBlue/10">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">BOTTOM LINE</p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">The window for early adoption is open but narrowing. The key strategic decision is not <em>whether</em> to adopt these technologies, but <em>sequencing</em>: GaN V and PD 3.2 are immediate requirements for any new charger design. Qi2.2 certification should be secured before Q4 2026 to capture holiday-season demand. Semi-solid-state batteries are the one technology where waiting 12 months is a defensible strategy, if you are willing to cede the premium tier to early movers. <a href="/contact/" class="text-brandBlue font-bold hover:text-brandOrange transition">Contact our team →</a> to discuss how these trends apply to your specific product roadmap.</p>
